Mxolisi Mngadi, News24IEC voting station. (Schalk van Zuydam, AP, file) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban &ndash; No intimidation has been reported during the ward 7 by-election in the uPhongolo municipality on Wednesday, the Electoral Commission of SA (IEC) said.All voting stations opened on time at 07:00 and nothing untoward had been reported, KwaZulu-Natal IEC spokesperson Thulani Ngwira said.They would remain open until 21:00. The results would be available on the IEC&rsquo;s results dashboard as soon as all votes had been tallied. The ANC, EFF, IFP, and NFP are taking part in the by-election.The ward became vacant when the ANC councillor, who won it during the August local government elections, died.Voter turnout for the ward in those elections was 46.84% and the ANC candidate got 55.62% of the vote, according to the IEC.On May 24, the IFP won 14 out of the 17 wards contested in the Nquthu municipality. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.